Android Developer with Kotlin

Looking for an Android Java/Kotlin developer to work on Android applications for farmers, agricultural machines, and Agri robots. Our company has developed one of the best farming apps on Google Play. All levels of experience are encouraged to apply.

We are looking for colleagues who want to help every farmer to feed the world by facilitating the transition to more productive and sustainable arable and orchard farming. By providing accessible intelligence and machine automation for high-quality fieldwork on every farm and under all conditions.

About the role

As a Native Android developer, you will develop and integrate new innovative features in the user interface and user flow of the Android application for farmers.

What You Will Be Doing:
• Integration with external devices (Bluetooth SPP/BLE, WiFi, Sockets, CAN BUS, GPS High precision devices, protocols with IOT sensors).
• Integration with back-end and high-loaded systems (RESTFul API, OAuth 2.0).
• Working with maps (GIS, Polygons, Heatmaps, custom tile providers, GeoJSON).

Skills:
• Strong experience in creating Android applications with Kotlin. Java and C++ as plus;
• Good knowledge of JavaCore;
• OpenGl 2.0 as plus;
• Understanding of architectural approaches MVVM and MVI;
• Design Patterns;
• Experience working with the development of Android APP from 1 year;
• Coroutines/RxJava;
• SQLite, room;
• Understanding of ООP, SOLID;
• Understanding of architectural approaches MVVM;
• Experience working with HTTP, JSON, XML та REST APIs;
• Experience working with Git (Git Flow);
• Agile / Scrum methodology approach.

What we offer:
• A fast-growing, dynamic company
• A strong social and ecological mission: we help farmers, we help the environment
• Competitive salary
• Flexible working hours
• Hybrid / working in an office
• Vacation and paid holidays according to legislation
• Remote type of working
